
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Oil Company Gas Station System

class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -fuelCard: FuelCard
  -invoices: List<Invoice>
  -status: CustomerStatus
}

enum CustomerStatus {
  ACTIVE
  SUSPENDED
  BLOCKED
}

class FuelCard {
  -cardNumber: String
  -customer: Customer
  -refuelTurns: List<RefuelTurn>
}

class RefuelTurn {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -amount: double
  -pump: Pump
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -month: Month
  -customer: Customer
  -refuelTurns: List<RefuelTurn>
  -totalAmount: double
  -discount: double
  -isPaid: boolean
}

class Payment {
  -id: int
  -invoice: Invoice
  -amount: double
  -date: Date
}

class Pump {
  -id: int
  -gasStation: GasStation
  -fuelType: FuelType
  -reservoirLevel: double
  -reorderLevel: double
  -criticalLevel: double
  -isBlocked: boolean
  -refuelTurns: List<RefuelTurn>
}

class GasStation {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -location: String
  -pumps: List<Pump>
  -dailyReport: DailyReport
}

class DailyReport {
  -reportDate: Date
  -pumpsToRefill: List<Pump>
  -currentLevels: Map<Pump, double>
  -quantitiesToOrder: Map<Pump, double>
}

class FuelType {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
}

class Refill {
  -id: int
  -pump: Pump
  -quantityAdded: double
  -date: Date
  -initiatedBy: GasStation
}

class BlockEvent {
  -id: int
  -pump: Pump
  -reason: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
}

' Relationships

Customer "1" -- "1" FuelCard : owns
FuelCard "1" -- "*" RefuelTurn : contains
RefuelTurn "1" -- "1" Invoice : belongs to
Invoice "1" -- "*" RefuelTurn : includes
Invoice "1" -- "*" Payment : has payments
Customer "1" -- "*" Invoice : receives
Customer "1" -- "*" Payment : makes

GasStation "1" -- "*" Pump : contains
Pump "1" -- "1" FuelType : uses
Pump "1" -- "*" RefuelTurn : handles
Pump "1" -- "0..1" BlockEvent : is blocked by
Pump "1" -- "*" Refill : refilled with

GasStation "1" -- "1" DailyReport : generates daily

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Customer**: Holds a fuel card and receives invoices. Can be in various states (Active, Suspended, Blocked).
- **FuelCard**: Used to track refuel turns without immediate payment.
- **RefuelTurn**: Represents each individual refueling event at a pump.
- **Invoice**: Generated monthly, includes all refuel turns from that month and applies discounts based on turnover.
- **Payment**: A record of a customer paying an invoice.
- **Pump**: Has a reservoir, can be blocked if below critical level or during refill.
- **GasStation**: Manages pumps and generates daily reports about fuel levels.
- **DailyReport**: Contains data about which pumps need refilling and how much fuel to order.
- **Refill**: Records when and how much fuel was added to a pump.
- **BlockEvent**: Tracks when a pump is temporarily blocked due to maintenance or safety reasons.

